## 9. Risk Factors

- **Industry-specific risks:** HVAC demand has a non-discretionary floor, but new-construction-weighted work is cyclical and interest-rate sensitive; rural southwestern South Dakota has a thin labor pool for skilled technicians.
- **Financial risks:** The decisive risk. A 4.0% SDE margin leaves no buffer — small cost or revenue swings push the business to breakeven or loss. The single-year disclosure prevents any quality-of-earnings or trend assessment. With $41,515 of SDE, there is no capacity to service acquisition debt (DSCR well below 1.0).
- **Operational risks:** Likely heavy owner dependence (the thin SDE is consistent with an owner-operator doing billable work). No GM or succession bench is disclosed. Loss of the owner-technician at close could be existential.
- **Regulatory / legal:** South Dakota mechanical/contractor licensing and standard OSHA, refrigerant-handling (EPA Section 608), and vehicle/DOT obligations apply. None verified — moot given the verdict.
- **Deal-specific conditions:** This deal is not curable into Buy Box range by negotiation. To even reconsider it, EarnedOut would need: (1) 3+ years of tax returns / P&Ls showing materially higher normalized EBITDA after add-backs than the listed $41,515; (2) a price renegotiation from ~36x to ≤4x EBITDA — a >85% reduction off earnings, only conceivable if the value is almost entirely real estate/equipment; and (3) confirmation of ≥10 FTE and a non-owner-dependent operating structure. The combination is implausible; recommend pass.

